a layer in the earth's stratosphere at an altitude of about 10 km (6.2 miles) containing a high concentration of ozone, which absorbs most of the ultraviolet radiation reaching the earth from the sun.

origin: mid 19th century: from German Ozon, from Greek ozein ‘to smell’.

definitions.definition: a colourless unstable toxic gas with a pungent odour and powerful oxidizing properties, formed from oxygen by electrical discharges or ultraviolet light. It differs from normal oxygen (O2) in having three atoms in its molecule (O3).
fresh invigorating air, especially that blowing on to the shore from the sea.
any of a class of unstable cyclic compounds formed by the addition of ozone to a carbon–carbon double bond.
convert (oxygen) into ozone.
definitions.example: when oxygen is ozonized there is a contraction in volume

definitions.definition: technical term for ozone layer.
